The paper deals with the problem of learning a one-hidden-layer neural network, which is a common topic in machine learning and falls under the category of deep learning. The paper also discusses the mathematical principles behind neural networks, which is related to the field of theoretical computer science. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
